description: Gapwaves AB engages in the research, development, production, and supply of wave antennas that provides wireless communication through the patented GAP waveguide technology. The company is headquartered in Goeteborg, Vastra Gotalands and currently employs 23 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2016-11-18. The firm operates as a developer of GAP waveguide packaging technology for millimeter wave and terahertz circuits and components. The firm's technology enables planar solutions with low losses, operating typically from 30 GHz to THz in applications such as antenna systems for Gigabit speed wireless communication and backhaul. The technology is based on an Artificial Magnetic Conductor that enables contactless propagation of electromagnetic waves. The firm offers a wide range of products, such as millimeter wave antennas for use in the V-band and E-band and easy-to-mount GAP flange adapters, among others.
name: Gapwaves AB
